		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's a single thing to buy/sell/manufacture, and it doesn't require serving double duty as a DMCA circumvention device (sigh).<br /><br />You could just decide that you're going to make something that could only be used by people with modchip-modded consoles. Is that a bigger or smaller proportion than the number of people who still have a parallel-port PS1? (I have no idea)<br /><br />Or you could decide to have two separate parts: a parallel-port modchip and a game disc. You could even include an SD interface, since flash is so much bigger than CDROMs now.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
