		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />All PlayStation 2 consoles are without the parallel port, despite their ability to run authentic game discs for the original PlayStation. I think that qualifies as &quot;enough of these PlayStations&quot;.<br /><br />The serial port was used for 2-player games, much like Game Link on a Game Boy. The parallel port was never used for a licensed peripheral, but several cheating tools used it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
